public final class RestDescription
extends com.google.api.client.json.GenericJson

Model definition for Discovery.RestDescription. This class models an object which will be transmitted to or from the Discovery service. To reduce the data transferred during service requests, you may remove members that contain data elements that your application does not need. For a detailed explanation, see: http://code.google.com/p/google-api-java-client/wiki/Json

setResponseHeaders

public void setResponseHeaders(com.google.api.client.http.HttpHeaders responseHeaders)
Sets the HTTP headers returned with the server response, or null. This member should only be non-null if this object was the top level element of a response. For example, a request that returns a single RestDescription would include the response headers, while a request which returns an array of RestDescription, would have a non-null response header in the enclosing object only.
